            <strong>DjiniLabs</strong>) (“Helpmaton”, “we”, “us”, “our”). The contracting entity for your use of the
            Service is shown on your checkout, invoice, or order confirmation.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <strong>Contact:</strong> <code>legal@helpmaton.com</code>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">2. Eligibility</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            You must be at least <strong>18 years old</strong> to use the Service. If you use the Service on behalf of
            an organization, you represent that you have authority to bind that organization, and “you” includes that
            organization.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">3. Accounts and security</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <li>You are responsible for keeping your account secure and for all activity under your account.</li>
            <li>You must provide accurate information and keep it up to date.</li>
            <li>You must promptly notify us of any unauthorized use or security incident relating to your account.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">4. The Service</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Helpmaton is a workspace-based platform that helps you create and manage AI assistants (“agents”), manage
            documents and knowledge, and connect via webhooks/APIs and third-party services.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            We may change, suspend, or discontinue any part of the Service at any time. We may also impose limits on
            features, storage, or usage.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">5. Acceptable use</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">You agree not to (and not to allow others to):</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <li>Violate applicable laws or regulations.</li>
            <li>Infringe or misappropriate others’ rights.</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Service, accounts, systems, or networks.</li>
            <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service (including by probing, scanning, or testing vulnerabilities).</li>
            <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract source code from the Service, except where prohibited by law.</li>
            <li>Use the Service to develop, provide, or support products or services that compete with the Service.</li>
            <li>Use the Service for high-risk activities where failures could lead to death, personal injury, or severe harm (e.g., medical, emergency response, critical infrastructure), unless you have our written permission.</li>
